      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Engineers ensure the bond works by using rough-surfaced rebar and chemical adhesion, which creates a mechanical interlock that prevents the steel from slipping inside the concrete matrix. Even deep inside the mix, this bond is critical because if the steel slipped, the rebar would act like a loose wire rather than a structural component, rendering the composite action useless. To mitigate potential failure points, specifications also require proper concrete cover to protect the rebar from corrosion, which would otherwise weaken the bond over time. Without this reliable connection, the foundation would lose its ability to share loads effectively during seismic events or heavy impacts.",
